  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "22 \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd 21 \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b9a \u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0baa\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The 22nd Amendment to the Constitution will soon be renamed Parliament as the 21st Amendment - Wijetasa Rajapaksa",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The 22nd Amendment to the Constitution will be published in the Gazette in a couple of days and will be tabled in Parliament shortly thereafter. Minister of Justice, Prisons Affairs and Constitutional Reforms Wijetasa Rajapaksa said the amendment would be renamed the 21st Amendment to the Constitution after it is tabled in Parliament.",
        "He was speaking at a press conference at the Government Information Department on Tuesday (28).",
        "The Cabinet approved the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution, a key condition for strengthening democracy and upholding the rule of law in the country, as expected by the people and the international community.",
        "The 22nd Amendment to the Constitution, approved by the Cabinet, will be published in the Gazette and will soon be tabled in Parliament. The bill will be published in the Gazette 7 days after it is included in the parliamentary agenda and the next steps will be taken thereafter.",
        "There is an ambiguous situation among the people regarding the number of constitutional amendments. The 21st Amendment is an amendment submitted by the United People's Power.",
        "A constitutional amendment has been submitted by the government due to difficulties in implementing it. That is why we consider this as the 22nd Amendment.",
        "As the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution was submitted by the Government, I withdrew the amendment I had proposed.",
        "However, the amendment, which is currently being approved by the Cabinet, will be renamed the 21st Amendment after it is tabled in Parliament. When the first debate on the 22nd Amendment begins, it will be referred to as the 21st Amendment.",
        "I believe that the 21st Amendment to the Constitution put forward by the United People's Power is unworkable.",
        "The minister also pointed out that the Supreme Court had ruled that a referendum was necessary to legislate every string in it."
      ],
